      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1-2">
         		<unclear>Year ?</unclear> twenty of the victorious king Mahendravarman<note>MaĪntiraparumaṉ in the original Tamil text.</note>.
         	</p>
        <p n="2-3">
         		<supplied reason="subaudible">This is the</supplied> stone <supplied reason="subaudible">of/for</supplied> Mārāṉ, a relative <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>makkaḷ</foreign>
          </supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Pālācirir, the ruler of Ciṟuppāḻ in the Mīvēṇṇāṭu, he who fell at the time of seizing cattle <supplied reason="subaudible">at</supplied> Kaṅkalūr.
         	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="commentary">
        <p>
         		Line beginnings not indicated in <bibl>
            <ptr target="bib:Kalvettu"/>
          </bibl>, here after <bibl>
            <ptr target="bib:Dayalan2005_01"/>
          </bibl>.
         	</p>
        <p>
         		Pālācirir, the ruler of Ciṟuppāḻ = Pālācirikar, ruler of Ciṟuppāl (INSPallava406) = Pālāyiriyar, ruler of Ciṟuppāl (INSPallava407).
         	</p>
